priations and Fees Authorized To Be Carried Over","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions authorizing fees collected under this chapter, and certain appropriations, to remain available until expended, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/607/s2"},"text":"section 2 of Pub. L. 99–607","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s42"},"text":"section 42 of Title 35","children":[],"tail":", Patents."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id7960011c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Trademark Fees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4203"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4203]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–554, as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13208"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III, § 13208","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1908"},"text":"116 Stat. 1908","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13208"},"text":"“Notwithstanding the second sentence of section 31(a) of the Trademark Act of 1946 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113/a"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1113(a)","children":[],"tail":"), the Under Secretary of Commerce for Intellectual Property and Director of the United States Patent and Trademark Office is authorized in fiscal year 2000 to adjust trademark fees without regard to fluctuations in the Consumer Price Index during the preceding 12 months.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/179/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–179, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2040"},"text":"107 Stat. 2040","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/103/179/s4"},"text":"“Effective on the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 1993","children":[],"tail":"], the fee under section 31(a) of the Trademark Act of 1946 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113/a"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1113(a)","children":[],"tail":") for filing an application for the registration of a trademark shall be $245. Any adjustment of such fee under the second sentence of such section may not be effective before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/204/s5/f/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–204, § 5(f)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1991-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 1991","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/105/1640"},"text":"105 Stat. 1640","children":[],"tail":", provided that fees established by Commissioner of Patents and Trademarks under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1113/a"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 1113(a)","children":[],"tail":" during fiscal year 1992 could reflect fluctuations during the preceding 3 years in the Consumer Price Index and could take effect on or after 1 day after such fees are published in the Federal Register and that the last sentence of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s31/a"},"text":"31 U.S.C. 31(a)","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s553"},"text":"5 U.S.C. 553","children":[],"tail":" did not apply to the establishment of such fees."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Similar provisions were contained in the following prior appropriation acts:","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/703/tI/s103/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–703, title I, § 103(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-19"},"text":"Nov. 19, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/4674"},"text":"102 Stat. 4674","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/607/s3/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–607, § 3(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3470"},"text":"100 Stat. 3470","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"reorganizationPlan","id":"id7960011d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Reorganization Plan No. 5 of 1950","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/609"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–609","children":[],"tail":" as subject to Reorganization Plan No. 5 of 1950, see note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1067"},"text":"section 1067 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id7960011e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id7960011f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of Commerce, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of Commerce, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 5 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1263"},"text":"64 Stat. 1263","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
